1. Select **File Storage Config**.

1. To use the PCF internal filestore, select the **Internal** option and click **Save**.

1. To use an external S3-compatible filestore for your Elastic
Runtime file storage, select the **External S3-Compatible Filestore** option and complete the following procedure:

  1. Enter the **URL Endpoint** for your filestore.
	
  1. Enter your **Access Key** and **Secret Key**.
      <p class="note"><b>Note</b>: If you are performing an upgrade from Elastic Runtime 1.5 to 1.6, do not modify the existing Bucket Name configuration or you may lose data. You must migrate your existing data before changing the configuration. See the <a href="upgrading-pcf.html#pcf16upgrade">Upgrading Ops Manager</a> topic for additional upgrade information.</p>

  1. Enter a **Buildpacks Bucket Name**.
	
  1. Enter a **Droplets Bucket Name**.
	
  1. Enter a **Packages Bucket Name**.

  1. Enter a **Resources Bucket Name**.
  1. Click **Save**.
